Yummmmm! This is my go to spot for Shawarma and Gyros! Everytime I go here they pack my plate with very tender, juicy, flavorful meat! I recommend the Shawarma Garden 4 Mixed Grilll and add gyro meat. Your tastebuds and your stomach will thank you. It comes with Beef Kabob, Kifta Kabob, Chicken Kabob, and Chicken Shawarma. It is the best way to try all of their delicious meats. The seasoning is so spot on and takes you for a flavor ride that you never want to end. I would say the Chicken Shwarma is my favorite, but that's by the smallest margin bc they are all great. Believe me, if you are looking for a quick casual Greek Spot with with Awesome Authentic spices and flavors, Shawarma Garden is where you wanna be.

I went in with a white friend of mine and was complete disrespected by the staff. I was literally the first individual to order. I ordered a simple wrap with falafel. I paid and sat  while waiting for my order to be prepared. My friend who ordered after me got his food... ten minutes go by and nothing... I watch as people enter and leave the establishment. I approach the individual who took my order, only to be YELLED at. He claimed “ I told you it would be 25 minutes when you ordered and you said that would be OK!”  He never mentioned anything about a wait time. I’m an extremely perceptive individual, so I mentally noted how much meat was on the spit, prior to ordering. I’m almost certain this was racially motivated. Why was every white customer given priority over me, when being served? I’m he tried covering his bigoted tracks, but unfortunately was unsuccessful. I hear the younger fry cook explain that he never even got my ticket! The order taker hid my ticket behind others just to make me wait. Pathetic. There was no apology issued. No one took any accountability for this action. I was simply left feeling unwanted and inferior.  As a newly relocated local they can forget about my business or that of my associates. Salam.

This is a fabulous neighborhood middle-eastern place. Along with the usual hummus/baba ghannouj/sharwma etc; they have a rice and lentil dishes too. If you go, try the Mujaddara. It is really well made. You can tell because the Lentils are cooked separately, added to the rice and that way the rice is not overcooked and finally the fried onions. It is a really nicely layered dish that shows that the people running the place care enough to make stuff that not only tastes good; but is authentic.  This along with the new Turkish restaurant that opened kitty corner makes this a good place to stop fr your middle eastern fill. If the long advertised Moroccan place opens too; we will be blessed.
